</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215BFFF5FF221CE4FED7FE6E" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215BFFF5FF221CE4FED7FE6E" blockId="9.[151,1436,2017,2044]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,394]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FF221CE4FE8FF81F" bold="true" box="[151,273,2017,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FF221CE4FE94F81F" bold="true" box="[151,266,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215BFFF6FEC71CE4FE44F81F" box="[370,474,2017,2043]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="14.7">14.7 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215BFFF6FD811CE4FD10F81F" box="[564,654,2017,2044]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
. Yellow on pronotal disc and dark yellow on posterior margin of the pronotum, scutellum, and corium (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FD961B92FDEFFF55" box="[547,625,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
); beneath uniformly yellow. Pronotal disc with punctures concolorous; posterior margin with a band of black punctures (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FD751BBEFC92FF31" box="[704,780,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with black punctures on black, small, isolated spots. Humeral angles projection short, dentiform (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FD591BDAFCA2FF1D" box="[748,828,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Anterior half of the costal margin of corium with punctures on large black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FE411A06FDA1FEF9" box="[500,575,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
); hypocostal ridge with few, black, small spots. Connexival segment VII with inner and posterior margin, and punctures black. Genital cup of the pygophore deeply excavated near the ventral rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FF7A1A4EFEB5FE82" box="[207,299,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Parameres short and triangular (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FD1B1A4EFC96FE82" box="[686,776,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 with distal margin sinuous ending in a sharp spine (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FF571A6AFEA2FE6E" box="[226,316,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF77667A2158FFF5FF221D8FFBCEF922" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" startId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" targetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22158FFF5FF221D8FFBCEF922" blockId="10.[151,1436,1674,1734]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FF221D8FFE8AF946" bold="true" box="[151,276,1674,1698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
Genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712158FFF5FE291D8EFDCBF946" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[412,597,1674,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciligramma" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FE291D8EFDCBF946" box="[412,597,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">G. graciligramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FDE91D8FFD11F946" bold="true" box="[604,655,1674,1698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B2158FFF5FDE91D8FFD11F946" box="[604,655,1674,1698]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C31265792158FFF4FF721DF1FD45FDD9" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22158FFF5FF721DF1FE45F826" blockId="10.[151,1437,1780,2023]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FF721DF1FECAF8EB" bold="true" box="[199,340,1780,1807]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FF721DF1FED3F8EA" bold="true" box="[199,333,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.4 times), black stripes thinner than in other species (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FB641DF1FA81F8EB" box="[1233,1311,1780,1807]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Antennal segments I–III with tiny black spots. Thorax: Pronotum wider than long (3 times); cicatrices delimited by grooves, weakly punctuated. Evaporatorium concolorous, dull, and smooth; lateral areas oval and punctured, not spotted (
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FF151C65FF6CF89F" box="[160,242,1888,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process green; anterior bifurcation with arms strongly acuminate; not spotted. Abdomen: connexivum weakly punctuated; segments III–VI medially with a barely visible callus. One trichobothrium in line and other lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22158FFF4FF721CC9FD3FFE6E" blockId="10.[151,1437,1780,2023]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02158FFF5FF721CC9FE9CF803" bold="true" box="[199,258,1996,2023]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772158FFF5FEA41CC9FE13F803" box="[273,397,1996,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">Fig. 6A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dark yellow, elongated (1.1 times), dorsal rim slightly projected over the genital cup. Posterolateral angles developed, inner margin black (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FCAE1B92FCEAFF56" box="[795,884,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Genital cup with large excavation, distal margin of the excavation (inner side of the ventral rim) black. Superior processes of the genital cup elliptic, touching dorsal rim. Parameres with anterior lobe triangular, posterior angle acute but not developed (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FB711BDAFA81FF1E" box="[1220,1311,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger concolorous, elongated (1.5 times); carina of the posterior surface restricted to basal half (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FB1F1A06FA9BFEFA" box="[1194,1285,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim excavation rounded, widely opened; expansions small, tumid and rounded almost fused with posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FF151A4EFF60FE82" box="[160,254,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface weakly convex beneath posterolateral angles; densely punctured with punctures of different sizes, concolorous to black (
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FD8E1A6AFD0AFE6E" box="[571,660,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721A97FD45FDD9" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721A97FE80FE49" bold="true" box="[199,286,402,429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772159FFF4FE9B1A96FE17FE4A" box="[302,393,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1674,1698]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,432,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-132@10.[151,1437,417,1650]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Genitalia of G. graciligramma sp.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500685/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 as long as wide, level with the distal margin of valvifer 9; not spotted. Valvulae 8 carinate, slightly visible between valvifers 8. Valvifer 9 longer than wide (1.4 times), laterals partially covered by valvifers 8. Laterotergites 8 longer than wide (1.5 times) distal spine exceeding laterotergites 9; only with few dark spots. Laterotergites 9 long, narrow, slightly curved, distally with a black spine; exceeding the band uniting the laterotergites 8, exceeding the level of segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF4FF721943FE44FD62" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF721943FE44FD62" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721943FED7FD85" bold="true" box="[199,329,582,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF721943FEDCFD85" bold="true" box="[199,322,582,609]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named for the head thin stripes, formed by punctation and sparse spots. From the Latin. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FAF51942FA02FD85" box="[1344,1436,583,609]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Gracilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FAF51942FA02FD85" box="[1344,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(thin) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FEB9196EFEEEFD61" authorityName="Poey" authorityYear="1868" box="[268,368,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Grammatidae" genus="Gramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FEB9196EFEEEFD61" box="[268,368,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Gramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(stripes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792159FFF4FF72198AFC8FFC66" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22159FFF4FF72198AFEB6FCF1" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF72198AFED7FD4D" bold="true" box="[199,329,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FF72198AFEDCFD4D" bold="true" box="[199,322,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The specimens studied here were kept in alcohol and lost most of their original color. Probably this species has the same color pattern found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FD3619B6FC8AFD29" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[643,788,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundicava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FD3619B6FC8AFD29" box="[643,788,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">G. fundicava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FCA919B6FCCDFD29" bold="true" box="[796,851,691,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B2159FFF4FCA919B6FCCDFD29" box="[796,851,691,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The size of the excavation of the genital cup, shape of the parameres, and distal margin of valvifers 8 sinuous, separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712159FFF4FC2419D2FBC2FD15" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[913,1116,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciligramma" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FC2419D2FBC2FD15" box="[913,1116,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">G. graciligramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02159FFF4FBD619D2FB05FD15" bold="true" box="[1123,1179,727,753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B2159FFF4FBD619D2FB05FD15" box="[1123,1179,727,753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="222" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from the other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
